elements.text:
Discover


  About:UXInterviewer is a application made so designers can practice real time whiteboarding challenges. 
            It is tailored for UI/UX students and profffesionals that want to prepare for their next interview 
                 Team consists of one designer one developer
                It will be a website, primarily webview 
                Users will be able to pick time limit, topics, and difficulty level
                  difficulty level is based off of operative definitions. 
                how they did would be based off of metrics 
                    - How they communicate
                    - Their design process (how specific/accurate it was)
                    - Speed 
                    - Did they solve the problem 

Who: UI/UX Students and professionals

Why: So they can prepare for real time whiteboarding challenges (no tools currently available)

Where: Website, private settings 

When: Before interviews, or ovearll everyday practice

What: An applciation for real time whiteboarding challenges

How: Users go on the site, they choose 

Constraints: 
    
Time - 2 months
Has to utilize an AI model - budget? (under free, 10/month, 20/month)
Has to be a webpage, website focused
Has to have different difficulty levels 
Has to have options to change time limit
categorize questions by topic 
User login 

Guidelines

Time split up into sprints - design -> development -> devlivery 


Incentives: 

Demo video in landing 

Budget

Free: Text to feedback -> No real time talking 
15/month - billed monthly  or  12.50/month -billed yearly -> real time talking, fast support, access to more tips and feedback
Figma for design, excalidraw for whiteboarding

React, nextjs, tailwind. 

History log of each level, metrics(leetcode style), description, time limit, category

User login: aws or something + google + two factor auth 


Research

Competitive analysis: 

Leetcode (interview prep)
    pro: interview prep, metrics, communty responses. 
    cons: Questions are not structured well/grouped into unhelpful groups (not patterns - by data structure) -  confusing UI. 

Designercize (designer prep) 
    pro: pick difficulty, time limit, and loads many different challge types, spamiblity , free!
    cons: gives challenge byt does not give feedback or suggest changes 

Sharpen (desitner prep)
    pro: you can pick category and lock different parts of the promtp you like. 
     cons: gives challenge byt does not give feedback or suggest changes 

Grammary (communication structure) 
    pro: good tone alaysis, delievery analysis, clairty, engagement analysis, etc
    cons: Subcategory of our application - generalized based off of tone and not by topic. 

User surveys

measured across 24 uxers throughout the HCC major at RIT. 

96% of designers wished there was a way for real time practice 
    "I believe having a real time whiteboarding application would really let me improve my communication throughout the interview, 
        it's something i struggle with"
    "I usually work on case studies, but it's hard to get feedback when i am working by myself"
  
45% have encounterer real time whiteboarding challenges in interviews'
    "I feel like there was a large empahsis on the design process and being able to communicate and learn quickly, which wasnt something i was used to at all" 

67% are not satisified with the design prep availble
    "I feel like the applications available are really limited."


Problem: How can we create an application that allows users to get reale time feedback on their whiteboarding challenge based on how they speak and perform? 



Define 

Isaac | 19 year old | male | HCC 

Wants: I really want to get better at the design process. I feel like its seomthing i really lack in 

Goal: Isaac wants real time feedback on improving his whiteboarding and design skills, but has no one to help him

Does'nt want: A confusing UI that lacks metrics. He wants to be able to track his prgoress at all times. 

Junheng | 20 years old | male | Web and mobile 

Wants: to prepare for his apple interview. 

Goal: Junheng has used applications like designercize and sharpen. He likes how he can easily get new prompts all the time, however, he
        wishes that there was a way to ask questions throughout his practice and get feedback when needed

Dislikes: the lack of tools availble today. Everything solves one problem - getting prompts - getting fake studies, etc 

Solution: Easy to access UI that allows users to pick difficulty level, time limit, and cycle through topics. Based on the version, people can either get real time feedback or post feedback. Users
                   can access old feedback through hsitory logs. Paid users can potentilaly screenrecord and vod review past challenges. 

Metric of success - deployed version with finished MVP. 



Develop

User flows

key


[Screen]           [Action]           [Decision]



User login

[screen] login - [decision] have account?
    
    - no - [action] register - [screen] register 
    
    - yes - [action] user login - [decision] - account exist/correct?
        - no - try again or register 
      
        -yes - [action] user inputs auth code - [decision] correct? 
            - no - [screen] try againtoast
            -yes - [screen] home


User Register

[screen] register - [decision] have account?
    
    - yes - [action] login - [screen] login
    
    - no - [action] user register - [decision] - account exist?
        - no - two factor auth to confirm - [decision] correct? 
            - no - [screen] try again toast
            -yes - [screen] home
      
        -yes - [action] login please, acc exists text - [screen] login



Level and prompt selection flow

[screen] home - [action] user selects next screen

[screen] - challenge - [action] user chooses topic -  [action] user chooses difficulty - [action] user chooses time limit
                                 -  [action] user chooses prompt  - [action] chooses real time feedback or nah - [action] starts - [screen] interview

[history screen] - [action] user goes through logs - [note] log shows topic, time, difficulty, prompt, overall score 
                              [decision] look at past info / try same prompt again

                                  -  look at past info  - [action] users look at individual interview information - [screen] past interview screen 
                                  - try again - [screen] confirmation modal - [decision] confirm? 
                                        - no - [screen] back
                                        - yes - [screen] interview (with same prompts)

    
[settings/profile screen] - [action] user selects 


[action] close - [screen] back

[action] settings - [screen] settings - [action] user selects tab 
             [screen] profile -[action] user selects 
                     [action] change username
                     [action] change email
                     [action] change password 
                          
             [screen] personalization
                    [action] user changes theme - [decision] premium? 
                            - no - get premium for custom themes 
                            - yes - [action] user can add new theme 
                          
                    [action] user changes font - [decision] premium? 
                             - no - get premium for custom fonts 
                            - yes - [action] user can change font
                            
             [screen] language
             [screen] subscription
    
           ---global flow in these screens--- 
           [action] user apply changes 
                        - [decision] same info/error/existing if username/email?
                                - yes - [screen] error toast
                                - no - [screen] changes saved toast
    
[action] logout - [screen] confirm modal - [decision] logout?
             - no - [screen] back
            - yes - [screen] login

elements.text:
About

Company Name: "Linkspace"

Overview: Linkspace is a prof. networking platform tailored for designs and creatives - think linkedin meets dribble..
Focused on genuine connection and mentorship rather than self promotion.

Mainly a web app, optimized for mobile too tho. 

Designer profiles

Networking feed

Mock interviews 

Skills Insight

Messaging & Invitations

Design Library 

Reseearch 

Visits settings when something goes wrong

Things that could be changes for data transparency

Acitivty data sharing 

analytics insight

public portfolio data 

profile discovery

data download 

Designers feel mentally tired navigatiing long settings list. 

Didnt realize there were interview specific hidden inside account seettings. They suggested surfacing those more 
prominently



78% use linkspace for interviews on desktop, but 60% check notis and availability on mobile. 

Tone: feels prof but human. 

String hieachy between categories (account, visiblity, privacy, communications)

Fiedntly, visiaul interface

DEFINE

Personas 

Jake | 19 | Designer 

Goal: Wants to check settings to modifiy his skills & make them public so other like minded designers can connect with him
Wants: Clear flow that allows him to add tags to his personal information
Dislikes: Navigiating long settings list 


Paul | 20 | Interviewee 

Goal: Does not like the automatic camera adjustments made in the interview software for linkspace, wants to edit it
Goal: Clear notice that she is ABLE to change this information
Dislieks: Lack of clear guideance and how to get rid of this nuance.

Answer: Create a settings page that is seperated into clear sections - based on a generalized settings page and specific needs given from
research, the designer's need, etc. 

DEVELOP

Users Flows
